HEADWORD: Globose
<hw>Glo*bose"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>globosus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having a rounded form resembling that
of a globe; globular, or nearly so; spherical.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

